><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/02 9:57:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://deneteth.freeservers.com/image/den2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction Good!</span><hr size=1> Hehe juste recently (first time last Monday) went in for a first introduction with the wyverns <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I plan on being there more often now... I'll sure say hello if you're around <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Deneteth <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmagedsnr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armaged SnR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/02 11:04:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction Good!</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> plus they don't agro for killing the wyverns.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>That is just so wrong.<br><br>Drakes do indeed aggro if you're beating on wyverns even with MAX COV.  The thing is though, Drakes have a relatively small aggro radius.  Even pulling a quad down the side of the runway is far enough from the patrolling drake that runs between the two rocks is safe that's how small their aggro radius is.<br><br>Another thing in CS to know is /pet get lost is your freind.  Drakes do <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NOT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> like flappy.  There have been several times now I have gotten hit by their dispell AE simply because they nuked flappy.  They totally ignored me afterwards, they just nuke flappy and go on their merry way.<br><br>That being said, be glad CS is empty for you!<br><br>On my server it's always crowded.  It is a very rare day when I get the wyverns to myself.  It's a pity too, cause with KEI by the time I get the last Wyverns killed, the first ones I killed are up again.<br><br><br>Lately though, it's gotten even worse on Ayonae Ro.<br>Folks are starting to setup camps at the end of the runway by the rock.  A group of folks mind you, and of course they are KOS to COV.  No matter how much aggro you have, you will lose 1 or 2 from a quad to them.<br><br>It's bad enough most times they don't want us in groups,, now those same groups are starting to take one of our best quadding zones over <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Aazumar Dracostarr<br>Raid Officer &lt;Divine Fate&gt;<br>Disciple of Solusek's 52nd Flame <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/02 12:08:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://deneteth.freeservers.com/image/den2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction Good!</span><hr size=1> Hum.. well i'll be careful with these Drake after all.<br><br>Another question for quadding in CS: when at 52, do you guys use the pillar of frost ? If yes, is it much resisted ?<br><br>Den <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uinusan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Inusan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 4:28:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction Good!</span><hr size=1> In my experience, more than one full resist per quad is rare.<br><br>I get enough partials, though, that it's very rare that all 4 mobs drop on the same cast of PoF - which means 1 or more extra casts of PoF, plus a single nuke to finish up a straggler.<br><br>Oh, and flux staff is your friend.<br><br>It's nice easy quadding for us, even with PoF. I dont have great gear, and very rarely have KEI...a full quad takes 85% mana on average...95% on a bad day, I'd say. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=225513" target="_new">Inusan Tohbi</a><br>53rd Erudite Channeler of Quellious<br>Member of <a href="http://www.immortal-spirit.com/" target="_new">Immortal Spirit</a><br>Tholuxe Paells Server<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usinnjatorix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sinnjatorix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 4:42:15 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?top