orum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 9:30:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://deneteth.freeservers.com/image/den2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction Good!</span><hr size=1> Newbie question but... what KEI stands for ? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uarmagedsnr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Armaged SnR</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 10:44:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction Good!</span><hr size=1> OMG, I honestly hope you're kidding me.<br><br>This one spell is the meat and potatoes of any Wizards career!<br><br>KEI (Kodiaks Endless Intillect)<br>60 Chanter Spell<br>Clarity 3, +25 WIS, +25 INT, +300 mana pool<br>Duration 2.5 to 4 hours (length effected by AA skills / focus items)<br><br>It's well worth making freinds with a 60 chanter for this, donating 100p for it, whatever.<br><br>Aazumar Dracostarr<br>Raid Officer &lt;Divine Fate&gt;<br>Solusek's 53rd Disciple <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/02 11:55:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://deneteth.freeservers.com/image/den2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction Good!</span><hr size=1> Nope not kidding <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :| --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/indifferent.gif ALT=":|"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I don't know that many 60 enchanters... most of us are still in the early 50s on FV (save the two or three ubers guilds). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udizzera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dizzera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/18/02 11:10:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction Good!</span><hr size=1> Aaahh... FV.  I am to understand that there are only like 4 KEI's going around on that server so far.  Yes KEI is worth the 100pp you spend on it.  You make it back in spades at wyverns!  Love KEI <br><br>/shudders<br>/e needs his KEIrack fix<br><br>KEI+damage focus+cast time focus= Uber fast quadding! <p><img src="http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/14/14731/pages/105006/dragonsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneilyxdawizofoz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neilyx DaWizofOz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/27/02 12:27:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personalpages.bellsouth.net/w/r/wrightpc/everquest/TheLetterN.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Faction Good!</span><hr size=1> Hmmm..<br><br>I have been seriously quadding in CS for the past week.  Im &quot;kindly&quot; to the Wyverns and quad over and around the drakes with no problem at all.<br><br>I do believe they will attack if they are caught in your AE - and the named Wyvern and the named Drake both will aggro on you if you quad within their aggo range - the other cobalst drakes pretty much ignore me.<br><br>Pillar of Frost is great for quadding Wyverns - this is one of those rare places where a cold spell <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> should</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be resisted but is not <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Biggest problem on my server is that once there are 8-11 people in the zone, the fights start - there just aren't enough mobs to go around and most people there are quadding or trying to <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ...<br> <p><p ALIGN=CENTER><img src="http://personalpages.bellsouth.net/w/r/wrightpc/everquest/NeilyxDaWizofOz.jpg" ></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uktadema.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ktadema</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/02 1:39:23 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Wyverns at 49 and 50</span><hr size=1> I single kited the wyverns at 49 and 50 when I couldn't get groups.  No Pillar of Frost back then of course, but it was still good experience doing them one at a time.  And the loot is nice, of course.  The Cobalt Scar portal makes the wyverns very accessable to wizards/druids.  On the Rodcet Nife server, however, I have never seen it where there isn't someone else quadding.  There is almost always 3-4 there in the wee hours of the morning, and it is too crowded most of the time. <p>***  Givins, 51st level Erudite Wizard, Rodcet Nife  ***</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uneilyxdawizofoz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neilyx DaWizofOz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/29/02 6:42:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://personalpages.bellsouth.net/w/r/wrightpc/everquest/TheLetterN.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wyverns at 49 and 50</span><hr size=1> Just a quick update on quadding in Cobalt Scar :<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   If you pull Wyverns near either the named Drake ( Azureake ) or the named Wyvern ( Yvolcran ) they will aggro on you.  Neither are that hard to kill <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> but</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> you will get a faction hit for killing them.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Before you start quadding Wyverns, just check where the Yvolcran is standing and verify the path that Azureake is flying. Then its just a matter of avoiding them.  Neither has a large aggro range so you just need to watch your step - its not that hard.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The wizard familiar - specifically the level 54 darke seems to aggro Azureake every now and then. I have been there for weeks with my flappy up and had no problems, then noticed another wizard getting attacked for no reason. Azureake will kill your familiar, then come for you.<br>To be safe do a /pet get lost once you zone in. The cold-based AE will de-buff you and this is the quickest, easiest way to lose you C3.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  On my server (luclin), once the zone has anywhere from 8-10 people it becomes over camped. It's relatively easy for a druid or a class with a pet to kill the drakes. It helps sometimes to ask them to do that.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Both the Drakes and the Wyvenrs run at the same speed so they can be quadded together in a group. I recommend that you have an item with &quot;Extended Range II&quot;  so that you can AE nuke from a distance and avoid the AE cold blast.<br><br><!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  there is almost NEVER a cleric in the zone. If you die, just pick your stuff up and keep quadding.<br><br><br> <p><p ALIGN=CENTER><img src="http://personalpages.bellsouth.net/w/r/wrightpc/everquest/NeilyxDaWizofOz.jpg" ></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uktadema.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ktadema</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/3/02 2:10:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wyverns at 49 and 50</span><hr size=1> Ouch, I can't agree about what the last post said about clerics never coming through CS.  I find that there are a few that pass through on the way to SG, WW and beyond.  After all, you have to go to CS to get any further.  I have to say, when I die in CS, I pick up most of my stuff, but I leave an item on my corpse so I can get that rezz when someone comes through that is willing to help.   <p>***  Givins, 51st level Erudite Wizard, Rodcet Nife  ***</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzeldara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeldara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(9/13/02 12:36:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=540.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> If you die in CS, good luck getting a cleric.  I've seen clerics passing by several times that I've gotten rezzes from, but on two occasions I've gotten Clerics from DL to come back with me to CS to give me a rez (I'm still bound in DL).  There are many good people out there to help you if you die <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessageRange?topicID=540.topic&start=21&stop=23>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=540.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=540.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=